Sony Online Entertainment today revealed EverQuest Online Adventures, an online roleplaying game for the PlayStation 2 set 500 years before the setting of its venerable PC cousin. SOE says that EverQuest Online Adventures will use the upcoming PS2 Broadband Adapter and will offer nine playable races, 13 character classes, customizable character features (sex, face, hair and more), more than 360 square miles of virtual game world to explore, a seamless environment (no load times and no rails), nine cities, eight different terrains, unique quests that promote player interaction and most importantly of all a 24/7 game world that will evolve without upgrades or additional software on the player side of things. SOE also promises that EverQuest Online Adventures will offer these firsts in console gaming: <br>
<br>
- Completely &quot;plug and play&quot; <br>
- First ever online only console game  (dont they all say this?   hehe)<br>
- Dedicated EverQuest Online Adventures servers <br>
- Low latency over a 56K modem <br>
- Interact with thousands of different characters each time you log on <br>
- A different experience every time you play <br>
