Interestingly, the PS2 version of the game is actually said to play a lot better than the PC original in certain respects. Line latency, for example, will be improved for the PS2 version. Everquest on the PC had to be designed to function with the lowest possible modem speed, 28.8, in mind. Since the PS2 will only have a 56K and higher connection, Sony can make that the lowest common denominator. What this basically means is that actions will be quicker across the network and the screens won't lag as often. <br>
