Massive Worlds <br>
Sony currently has 43 separate world servers, each supporting thousands of gamers, for Everquest; a number that will more than double once the PS2 version is introduced. &quot;Each world should support at least 3,000 people simultaneously who can go wherever they want,&quot; says Humble. The worlds are usually divided by race, but you can often travel from server to server. &quot;There are no zones or restrictions on players going anywhere.&quot; And what happens if you actually manage to go everywhere? Well, that's another beauty of Everquest. Every so often Sony releases new update packs that feature new areas and items for a relatively low price. Sony intends to do something similar with the PS2 version, but details haven't been locked down yet. Either way, Sony maintains that default game of Everquest Online Adventures will hold months of storyline and gameplay -- more than that of your typical console RPG. <br>
